 The intervention group will be received 100 milligrams per day of hydrocortisone on the first three day the taper off, whereas the control group will be received 200 milligrams per day of hydrocortisone on the first three day the taper off.

 Hyperglycemia rate will be monitored every 6 hours after hydrocortisone is started until 24 hours after it is stopped.

 Also, 28-day mortality will be follow after hydrocortisone is started.

